Ravi Beefnah parked his £35,000 Audi A5 outside the dealership in Chelmsford . 
  He claims the car uses a litre of oil every time he fills it up . 
  The 34-year-old parked his car as a warning to other buyers of the car . 
  Mr Beefnah claims Audi failed to resolve his complaint about the engine and fix it . 
  He is taking the dealership to court and is demanding £9,000 to fix his car . 
  Audi admits there is a problem with the engine but has offered to fix the car free of charge . 
 